            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🌾 F1 | Tailtean Plains",
              "description": "> Once the stage for the decisive battle that ended the War of Heroes, the Tailtean Plains stretch far into the horizon, their golden grasses whispering with echoes of ancient triumphs and terrible losses. The land is quiet now, almost reverent, but the weight of history clings to the air like morning fog.\n\nTattered banners still flutter from broken pikes embedded deep in the soil. It's said that during the war, the skies above Tailtean wept fire and the ground turned red with spilled blood. Some say if you listen closely, you can hear phantom war cries carried by the wind.\n\nA circle of standing stones crowns a small rise to the east. A single white flower blooms at the center. A rare Tailtean lily.",
