          "F2": {
            "channelId": "1431901269748093134",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🏞️ F2 | Remire Village",
              "description": "> Once a quiet farming village nestled along the kingdom’s southern border, Remire bears the scars of the tragedy that unfolded there years ago—a horror few dare speak of, yet all remember. Though the homes have been rebuilt and the fields re-sown, an uneasy hush clings to the narrow paths and shuttered windows, as if the land itself remains wary of strangers.\n\nIn the heart of the village stands an aging forge, its chimney always puffing, its anvil never quiet. The blacksmith—an old veteran of the Southern Church wars—still plies his trade with a stubborn gleam in his eye. Rows of aged swords and battered axes hang on rusted racks, each one with a story, a scar, or a name etched into the steel. He offers to repair what others might discard, saying, “Old blades still bite hardest—if you treat ’em right.”\n\nLanterns flicker at dusk, casting long shadows across the stone paths, and though many buildings lie hollow, the village endures. Some say it survives out of habit.",
              "image": null,
              "clues": []
