            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🛤️ F3 | Rhodos Coast Road",
              "description": "> The well-worn road that stretches along the Rhodos Coast is a lifeline connecting Garreg Mach Monastery to the outposts and towns scattered along the eastern coast of Fódlan. Though maintained by Church envoys, the path is not without danger-its twisting bends and craggy passes are ripe for bandit ambushes and monster sightings.\n\nThe Rhodos Coast features a cemetery that is held sacred by the Church of Seiros. In Imperial Year 1180, the Western Church seized the cemetery in a direct provocation of the Central Church.\n\nThe air is tinged with salt and the faint clang of metal...\n\nOn the path sits an overturned merchant cart. Goods spill out onto the road and whoever this cart once belonged to is now nowhere to be seen. Further down you an see Lysithea sitting on a rock, as if she is waiting.",
