            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🏹 G3 | Ancient Battlements",
              "description": "> You arrive at the Ancient Battlements, where shattered stone ramparts rise from the earth like the ribs of some buried titan. The air is heavy with age and memory—each broken wall and crumbled turret a monument to battles long past. These are the forgotten outposts of Adrestia’s old frontier, once bristling with archers and war cries, now overtaken by creeping moss and the silence of time.\n\nOld banners hang in tatters from weathered poles, their colors bleached by sun and rain. Arrowheads litter the ground, half-buried in dry soil, and deep gouges in the stone hint at violent sieges. A rusted ballista sits overturned, its bolts scattered like bones.\n\nThere’s a cracked stairwell leading downward into a collapsed watchtower. Could something be hidden below? A crow watches from a broken merlon, unmoving.",
