            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🌉 E4 | Bridge to Cathedral",
              "description": "> Stretching across a wide chasm beneath Garreg Mach Monastery, the bridge is a majestic span of pale stone lined with carved balustrades and weather-worn statues of saints and wyverns.\n> \n> Moss creeps up between the flagstones, hinting at the age of the structure, while fluttering banners in House colours catch the wind overhead.\n> \n> Though there are no shifts in elevation, the sheer length of the bridge gives it a feeling of ceremonial grandeur—as though crossing it is a rite in itself. \n\nMarianne looks out across the water, but shifts her attention to you as you approach.",
