          "F4": {
            "channelId": "1431901362161193000",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🪖 F4 | Gloucester Front",
              "description": "> Just beyond the fortified eastern wall of Garreg Mach, the rolling highlands give way to a strip of contested earth known informally as the Gloucester Front. Once a peaceful crossroads between the monastery and the lands of the Leicester Alliance, the area now bears signs of quiet militarization—flattened grass from boot drills, hastily erected palisades, and war banners half-lowered in the wind.\n\nHouse Gloucester, ever keen to defend its influence, maintains a guarded watch here, wary of incursions from both imperial forces and internal unrest. Scouts peer from weather-worn towers at the shifting treelines, while armored riders patrol the perimeter with cold precision. The air is sharp with the scent of oil, steel, and anticipation. There are no active battles - yet.",
