          "F5": {
            "channelId": "1431901398878126242",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🏹 F5 | Red Canyon Watch",
              "description": "> The land east of the monastery begins to steepen here, its grasslands giving way to a series of jagged ridges and red-stained cliffs that hint at ancient upheavals. This is the edge of the territory known in legend as the Red Canyon-sacred ground, sealed off by the Church after a cataclysm lost to most histories.\n\nThough the true heart of the canyon lies far deeper and to the south, a small outpost was once established here by the Knights of Seiros to keep vigil over the area. Now, it lies half-forgotten: moss overtakes its broken watchtowers, and scattered relics of its former occupants remain untouched. Birds refuse to nest here.\n\nSome scholars claim the earth remembers what happened in the Red Canyon. Fewer still dare to ask what it’s trying to forget. On one walk wall you see a boulder that appears out of place. As if it's been recently moved.",
