            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🌋 G6 | Valley of Torment",
              "description": "> You stand at the edge of a forsaken expanse where life has long since fled. The air here is thick with heat and heavy silence, broken only by the occasional crack of shifting stone or the deep, guttural groan of the scorched earth below.\n\nThe ground is a jagged tapestry of blackened rock, scorched orange clay, and crimson ash—warped and blistered from some ancient calamity. Faint wisps of sulfurous smoke drift up from unseen fissures, and the scent of brimstone clings to every breath.\n\nOnce verdant and alive, the land now glows faintly with ember-veined rock, casting a dim, eerie light even at dusk. Twisted remnants of trees, long petrified by flame, stand like charred sentinels watching over a grave of memories.\n\nIn the distance, skeletal ruins pierce the haze—structures once proud now broken and half-swallowed by the earth. Here, the world feels thinner, as though something beneath it still stirs.",
