          "F7": {
            "channelId": "1431901493379993683",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🌊F7 | Rhodos Coast",
              "description": "> A stretch of wind-swept cliffs that plunges sharply into the restless sea, the Rhodos Coast marks the outer edge of Fódlan's eastern realm. Salt hangs heavy in the air, carried by fierce gusts that churn the water into frothy eddies. Offshore, jagged rocks break the surf—silent sentinels born of ancient upheaval.\n\nCoast-hogged paths wind along crumbling ridges, where moss-covered stone keeps its grip. Ancient statues—worn by spray and time—dot the coastline, icons to a sea deity once revered by sailors. A lone ship’s wheel lies half-buried in the sand, as though washed ashore from a forgotten wreck. A gull drifts overhead, staking claim to abandoned driftwood and barnacle-encrusted hull fragments.\n\nUnderfoot, the pebbled beach is littered with fragments of pottery and bits of crest-bearing rings—lost in the tides, now silent relics telling stories of smugglers or exiled noble households. At the water’s edge, a carved seashell glows faintly blue.",
