            "baseContent": {
              "title": "Kokori Forest",
              "description": "> You're in The Kokori Forest - a lush, green picturesque village nestled within the woods, adorned with treehouses, a small pretty stream, and fairies lighting up the air. The forest is full of friendly Kokori villagers, a tribe of small child-like beings that call the Kokori Forest home, and never age into adulthood.\n\nThere's a winding pathway through the village adorned with rocks and shrubs off to the side that makes it easy to navigate.\n\nThere are various houses you can visit, a small shop, and a number of the villagers seem eager to speak to you.\n\nThe village is scorned by cliffs with thick vines crawling up them, with a waterfall flowing one of the cliffs forming the basis of the stream that runs through the village supplying water to the Kokori.\n\nHowever, there's an angry looking kid standing in front of the entrance to the Great Deku Tree - you better talk to him before you try to navigate to where the Great Deku Tree is.",
